deck: Special trade that collects three self-contained stories of Avatar's Night of the Living Dead series.
description:
Day of the Undead is another Night of the Living Dead collection reprinting three stories from previous installments written by Mike Wolfer, John Russo, and Edison George and published by Avatar Press in 2012.

  • George A. Romero's Night of the Living Dead: Just A Girl #1
  • Night of the Living Dead: Holiday Special #1 - "Do Not Open Until Christmas"
  • Night of the Living Dead: 2011 Annual

For a special price to attract new readers - 64 pages for $2.99 - this collection was published around Halloween and prior to the launch of the new ongoing series Night of the Living Dead: Aftermath.
name: Night of the Living Dead: Day of the Undead

deck: Shaman King Kazenban is the perfect edition of Shaman King that has the true ending.
description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Shman Kingu Kanzen-Ban)

Shaman King is originally created by Hiroyuki Takei, and in 2009, Shueisha republished the original series in Kanzen-Ban or "Perfect" volumes, which rearranged the series into 27 volumes (March 3, 2008-April 3, 2009) and 300 chapters. It should be noted that in the original collections there were only 285 chapters (with the last being a special ending that had not been serialized). This was due to the premature ending of the series in Weekly Shonen Jump which many felt necessitated a true ending that was given as part of this edition.

The Shaman King series has two formats of the Kanzenban: the 27 volume series and the 16 volume series (budget remix version).
name: Shaman King Kanzenban

description: Shaman King Mentalite is a guide book on the Shaman King franchise, and it has a bonus story, too. The bonus story is a short called "Snake's Legs" which serves as an epilogue to the series of short stories entitled Funbari no Uta.

description:
The adventures of Bandette, a young costumed artful dodger, leader of a group of urchins dedicated to serving justice, except when thieving proves to be a bit more fun. The story of Bandette treads a thin line between Tintin and Nancy Drew, with a few costumes thrown in. Bandette and her crew at turns join forces and cross swords with the mysterious master thief known only as Monsieur, and one B.D. Belgique, perhaps the most harassed police inspector of all time.

Collected Editions

  • Bandette: Presto! (#1-5)
  • Bandette: Stealers, Keepers! (#6-9)
  • Bandette: The House of the Green Mask (#10-13)
name: Bandette
